</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4882/thicker-workspace-button-border-in-i3bar/?comment=4884#comment-4884</link><description>Since version 4.8 i3 tries to compensate for high-resolution displays. So if you have a screen with a resolution well above the common 96 dpi ("Retina", "Ultra-HD") i3 may use two pixel for these borders instead of one.</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Oct 2014 16:10:15 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4882/thicker-workspace-button-border-in-i3bar/?comment=4884#comment-4884</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Maarten for &lt;p&gt;Hi,
